PEP 8 -  Python Enhancement Proposal
Standard how code is disigned

peps.python.org/pep-0008

"Readability counts"
A style guide is about consistency.
Consistency with this style guide is important.
Consistency with a project is more important.
Consistency within one one module or function is the most important.

- Indentation
- Tabs or Spaces?
- Maximum line length
- Blank lines
- Imports

pylint - programm that statically analysis the code (pycodestyle.pycqa.org)  #noisy
pip install pylint

For formatting:
- pycodestyle (pycodestyle.pycqa.org)
- black (black.readthedocs.io; pip install black)
  In terminal black file_name.py  --> reformatted file_name.py
